WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.710 --> 00:00:03.370
Get moving right now, get moving right now

3
00:00:03.590 --> 00:00:06.460
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

4
00:00:12.770 --> 00:00:15.500
Setting out all on our own to cross the endless sea,

5
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.060
you know what we're searching for

6
00:00:18.860 --> 00:00:21.810
The worldwide enigma, treasures undiscovered

7
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:23.940
Picking's ripe, so let's go explore

8
00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:27.960
We're all so excited, our hearts can't keep quiet

9
00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:29.710
Nothing left to do but press on

10
00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:35.590
Trailing after footprints left by the dreamers before us

11
00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:39.390
Stormy nights can try their best to sink us

12
00:00:39.390 --> 00:00:42.390
We'll sail on, if we just stick together

13
00:00:42.390 --> 00:00:46.540
Try and stop us if you can

14
00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:47.860
We always pull through

15
00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:51.590
Get moving right now, get moving right now

16
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.550
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

17
00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:57.140
Even if we sometimes shed tears,

18
00:00:57.230 --> 00:01:00.580
and want to hide them from prying eyes

19
00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:03.520
But go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

20
00:01:03.690 --> 00:01:06.520
Run the direction the compass points in

21
00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:09.230
All our dreams are straight ahead it says

22
00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:11.400
So don't sit back, let's chase it

23
00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:21.490
Get moving right now, get moving right now

24
00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:24.540
We have to pull through ahead of them all

25
00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:27.120
If we hold firm and stand our ground,

26
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.540
I know the future's within our grasp

27
00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:33.630
So go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

28
00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:36.510
The world's our oyster, it's waiting for us

29
00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:38.930
All the sadness and the joy we see,

30
00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:41.430
let's etch it in our hearts

31
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:54.010
<b>Ohara vs. The World Government</b>

32
00:01:59.060 --> 00:02:00.520
What's the matter, Robin?

33
00:02:01.980 --> 00:02:04.230
Was my mom here?

34
00:02:05.480 --> 00:02:10.400
What are you saying?
Why would your mother be on Ohara?

35
00:02:11.570 --> 00:02:12.950
...I must sever ties.

36
00:02:12.950 --> 00:02:16.450
I can't let her become known
as a criminal's daughter.

37
00:02:17.530 --> 00:02:19.410
What's this about all of a sudden?

38
00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:21.250
W-Well...

39
00:02:21.250 --> 00:02:22.870
Oh, that's right! There's trouble!

40
00:02:23.460 --> 00:02:28.170
I heard that Marine battleships are coming
to arrest all the scholars here!

41
00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:31.550
Is the town blowing things out of proportion?

42
00:02:32.050 --> 00:02:33.010
What?

43
00:02:33.010 --> 00:02:35.760
There are no battleships.

44
00:02:35.760 --> 00:02:39.760
We did hear about
a government ship making landfall,

45
00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:43.890
but it's for an investigation,
likely more rigorous than ever.

46
00:02:43.890 --> 00:02:47.400
Listen, Robin, although
the government representatives are here,

47
00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:51.400
you absolutely cannot tell them
that you're an archaeologist.

48
00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:56.860
Since you're such a small child, no one will
think that you're a scholar. Understood?

49
00:02:58.490 --> 00:02:59.620
Move!

50
00:03:01.290 --> 00:03:04.160
Stop what you're doing!
Hands in the air, and step outside!

51
00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:07.080
Now, that's going too far.

52
00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:12.510
The Ohara Research Center is suspected
of a criminal offense: deciphering poneglyphs!

53
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:16.470
We must conduct a thorough search,
so everyone outside. Now!

54
00:03:17.010 --> 00:03:19.010
Treat this place with care.

55
00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:23.350
The treasures kept here are
more valuable than you can imagine.

56
00:03:23.350 --> 00:03:25.390
You're wasting your breath!

57
00:03:25.390 --> 00:03:26.390
Get him out!

58
00:03:26.390 --> 00:03:27.480
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

59
00:03:27.810 --> 00:03:29.610
Listen up, townspeople!

60
00:03:29.610 --> 00:03:35.450
It is our suspicion that the scholars of this island
are devils plotting to destroy the world!

61
00:03:35.450 --> 00:03:36.820
What?! Why?!

62
00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:41.490
They're world-renowned scholars
and the pride of this island!

63
00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:45.660
And so, we will conduct an extensive
search of the entire island!

64
00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:49.040
In the meantime, those
uninvolved in archaeology

65
00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:53.630
will prove it with identification and board
the evacuation ship at the western shore!

66
00:03:53.630 --> 00:03:56.130
An evacuation ship?
Is that really necessary?

67
00:03:56.130 --> 00:03:59.550
If it's the scholars' problem,
we have nothing to do with it.

68
00:03:59.550 --> 00:04:02.010
We shouldn't be required to leave the island.

69
00:04:02.010 --> 00:04:04.850
It's merely our duty
to pass that message to you.

70
00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:09.150
What happens to those
who ignore our warning...

71
00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:12.860
is none of our concern.

72
00:04:18.150 --> 00:04:19.110
Leave town!

73
00:04:19.110 --> 00:04:20.780
Evacuate to the western shore!

74
00:04:20.780 --> 00:04:23.030
The World Government is up to something!

75
00:04:28.040 --> 00:04:31.790
I've been shot! Th-This is the end!
I'm a goner, dammit!

76
00:04:31.790 --> 00:04:33.710
Tell the higher-ups...

77
00:04:33.710 --> 00:04:36.300
to give my position as chief to my boy!

78
00:04:36.300 --> 00:04:38.590
Chief, please take a close look.

79
00:04:38.590 --> 00:04:41.090
The bullet barely grazed your jacket.

80
00:04:41.090 --> 00:04:42.180
Oh, I see.

81
00:04:45.470 --> 00:04:47.100
I won't miss next time.

82
00:04:48.390 --> 00:04:52.560
Well, if it isn't the fugitive
who craftily escaped the Marines' prison!

83
00:04:52.560 --> 00:04:56.570
Fancy seeing you on this island, Nico Olvia!

84
00:04:56.570 --> 00:05:00.820
You kept denying any connection
to the Oharan scholars, yet here you are.

85
00:05:00.820 --> 00:05:05.830
It's almost as if you're telling us
this is where you call home...

86
00:05:06.450 --> 00:05:10.580
and that the scholars here are
guilty of the same crimes as you.

87
00:05:10.920 --> 00:05:14.540
Just my being here
isn't proof enough for that.

88
00:05:15.710 --> 00:05:18.800
I'm sure you've come up with lots of excuses.

89
00:05:18.800 --> 00:05:21.180
You're a smart woman, after all.

90
00:05:21.180 --> 00:05:23.180
But none of that matters anymore.

91
00:05:23.180 --> 00:05:26.810
We have no need to prove
your connection to Ohara.

92
00:05:26.810 --> 00:05:29.560
If we dig up every square meter of this island,

93
00:05:29.560 --> 00:05:33.770
evidence of your poneglyph
research is bound to turn up.

94
00:05:33.770 --> 00:05:37.480
The government estimates a 100 percent
probability of this outcome.

95
00:05:38.070 --> 00:05:42.660
For six years now you've eluded us
at every turn, escaping from sea to sea.

96
00:05:42.660 --> 00:05:45.740
Capturing you is just
the start for the government.

97
00:05:45.740 --> 00:05:50.200
We've apprehended many
a poneglyph researcher across the world,

98
00:05:50.200 --> 00:05:53.460
each time searching for a connection to Ohara.

99
00:05:53.960 --> 00:05:55.460
Can you guess why?

100
00:05:56.790 --> 00:05:58.920
No...! You'll make an example of Ohara?!

101
00:05:59.380 --> 00:06:00.840
Exactly!

102
00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:05.390
If the holy land of archaeology were destroyed,
all scholars would get the message.

103
00:06:06.140 --> 00:06:11.390
Then the world would see what happens
to those who dare research the Void Century!

104
00:06:11.730 --> 00:06:15.770
Then, those Marine battleships standing by...

105
00:06:16.360 --> 00:06:19.940
Hey now... Just how much do you know?

106
00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:21.280
You are correct.

107
00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:25.530
They are there to ensure
that not one criminal escapes.

108
00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:29.790
But for legitimacy, we must first verify
a crime has been committed.

109
00:06:29.790 --> 00:06:32.040
We're not pirates, after all.

110
00:06:32.040 --> 00:06:35.000
That's why I came all this way.

111
00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:40.760
I need to conduct a thorough investigation
of the island and evacuate those who aren't involved.

112
00:06:40.760 --> 00:06:42.210
Yes, that's why I'm here.

113
00:06:43.470 --> 00:06:44.550
Get her.

114
00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:59.320
Hey, stop it! The books here
are a world treasure!

115
00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:01.150
Another one?! Take him outside!

116
00:07:01.150 --> 00:07:01.940
Come with me!

117
00:07:01.940 --> 00:07:03.400
Dammit, you bastards!

118
00:07:03.860 --> 00:07:05.740
There must be a hidden room!

119
00:07:05.740 --> 00:07:07.370
Make sure you find it!

120
00:07:07.410 --> 00:07:11.330
<b>Northwest Coastline, Ohara
(Saul's Present Location)</b>

121
00:07:11.990 --> 00:07:13.960
This is terrible!

122
00:07:14.460 --> 00:07:18.830
The battleships are already within sight!

123
00:07:20.420 --> 00:07:22.000
Is this all of them?!

124
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:25.380
Now, gather all the scholars here!

125
00:07:25.380 --> 00:07:27.930
Look. The scholars have been captured.

126
00:07:27.930 --> 00:07:29.430
What could they have done?!

127
00:07:29.430 --> 00:07:32.140
They said the scholars
wanted to destroy the world!

128
00:07:32.140 --> 00:07:33.350
That can't be true.

129
00:07:33.350 --> 00:07:35.350
Where's the evacuation ship?!

130
00:07:35.350 --> 00:07:37.310
It's at the western shore! Hurry!

131
00:07:37.650 --> 00:07:40.020
Hurry up and get to the western shore!

132
00:07:40.020 --> 00:07:41.110
Robin.

133
00:07:41.570 --> 00:07:43.570
There's an evacuation ship.

134
00:07:43.570 --> 00:07:46.570
There's no telling what the government will do.

135
00:07:46.570 --> 00:07:48.030
Hurry and head that way too!

136
00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:51.990
No! Even if I get on that ship,
the people there won't be nice!

137
00:07:51.990 --> 00:07:53.740
I'm staying here with you guys!

138
00:07:53.740 --> 00:07:54.620
Robin...

139
00:07:54.620 --> 00:07:55.870
Just like you guys, I'm a–

140
00:07:55.870 --> 00:07:57.540
Just go already!

141
00:08:00.420 --> 00:08:02.210
Working hard, men?

142
00:08:02.210 --> 00:08:04.630
– We appreciate the visit, Chief!
– We appreciate the visit, Chief!

143
00:08:04.630 --> 00:08:10.760
I tell you, this is the last place
I expected to run into a ferocious animal.

144
00:08:14.220 --> 00:08:16.680
I was nearly killed.

145
00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:18.690
Olvia!

146
00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:20.520
Olvia...

147
00:08:21.230 --> 00:08:22.730
All right, listen carefully.

148
00:08:22.730 --> 00:08:24.440
This woman is a fugitive.

149
00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:28.950
Her companions were recently put to death
for deciphering the ancient script.

150
00:08:28.950 --> 00:08:32.280
However, we still don't know
who the ringleader is.

151
00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:38.540
Of course, if you guys are connected
to this woman, this will go much smoother.

152
00:08:40.370 --> 00:08:42.840
They're treating her so cruelly...

153
00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:46.800
Robin, go to the evacuation ship. Hurry!

154
00:08:46.800 --> 00:08:47.630
Robin...

155
00:08:53.140 --> 00:08:54.510
Robin!

156
00:08:57.350 --> 00:08:58.930
You've...

157
00:09:03.770 --> 00:09:06.280
gotten so big!

158
00:09:07.360 --> 00:09:09.240
Olvia...

159
00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:14.490
Wh-What have they done?!

160
00:09:14.490 --> 00:09:16.990
Have they no respect for the library?!

161
00:09:16.990 --> 00:09:19.540
To think they'd take things this far...

162
00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:22.120
Oh, what a spectacle!

163
00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:27.000
Hello? Is this the chief?!

164
00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:28.210
Yeah, it's me.

165
00:09:28.210 --> 00:09:30.050
We've found it!

166
00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:31.590
In a hidden room underground,

167
00:09:31.590 --> 00:09:36.470
there are research papers on ancient texts
and a large stone believed to be a poneglyph!

168
00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:38.180
All right. Well done!

169
00:09:42.020 --> 00:09:44.400
Well then, scholars of Ohara...

170
00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:48.360
that means you all get the death sentence!

171
00:09:48.780 --> 00:09:55.990
It is indeed regrettable that the world's
premier archaeologists will lose their lives today.

172
00:10:00.120 --> 00:10:02.120
Man, what a letdown.

173
00:10:02.120 --> 00:10:04.130
My job's done here!

174
00:10:04.130 --> 00:10:06.500
All I can do now
is report it to the Five Elders.

175
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:07.590
Roger.

176
00:10:09.340 --> 00:10:12.720
Professor, are they really going
to kill you?! They're lying, right?!

177
00:10:12.720 --> 00:10:15.050
Just for reading ancient text?! Why?!

178
00:10:15.430 --> 00:10:17.560
You dumb brat!

179
00:10:17.560 --> 00:10:23.390
The purpose of their research is to revive
a powerful weapon and commit mass murder!

180
00:10:23.730 --> 00:10:26.480
That's a lie! That's not at all what they're doing!

181
00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:28.400
Robin, please stop.

182
00:10:28.400 --> 00:10:30.860
As an errand boy, he wouldn't understand.

183
00:10:30.860 --> 00:10:31.860
What'd you say?!

184
00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:35.740
Is it really the weapon itself
that the government is afraid of?

185
00:10:35.740 --> 00:10:36.870
– Professor!
– Professor Clover!

186
00:10:36.870 --> 00:10:38.580
It's connected, Chief.

187
00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:39.740
Okay.

188
00:10:39.740 --> 00:10:41.540
This is good timing.

189
00:10:40.790 --> 00:10:41.540
Huh?!

190
00:10:41.540 --> 00:10:46.540
If I'm doomed to die, let me first speak
to the Five Elders, the world's leaders.

191
00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:50.050
We, the scholars of Ohara,
have dedicated many years to our research,

192
00:10:50.050 --> 00:10:54.180
and while we must stop halfway now,
we have a hypothesis about the Void Century.

193
00:10:54.180 --> 00:10:56.550
I'd like to report it to them.

194
00:10:57.510 --> 00:10:58.760
What a waste of time....

195
00:10:58.760 --> 00:10:59.430
Hey.

196
00:10:59.430 --> 00:10:59.970
Yes, sir.

197
00:10:59.970 --> 00:11:02.430
Robin, get away from here now!

198
00:11:02.930 --> 00:11:05.440
Listening to what I'm about to say is a crime.

199
00:11:06.440 --> 00:11:08.110
Professor...

200
00:11:08.110 --> 00:11:11.360
Hey, apparently the scholars
have been found guilty.

201
00:11:11.360 --> 00:11:12.570
Is that true?!

202
00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:16.530
Hey! Marine battleships are
sailing this way from the east!

203
00:11:16.910 --> 00:11:20.330
They're gonna do something!
Let's hurry to the evacuation ship!

204
00:11:20.780 --> 00:11:22.040
Wh-What the...?!

205
00:11:22.040 --> 00:11:23.790
It's a giant!

206
00:11:26.670 --> 00:11:29.630
Where are you, Robin?!

207
00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.460
You need to hurry
and escape from this island!

208
00:11:38.800 --> 00:11:41.180
Has the buster call been sounded yet?

209
00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:43.640
We're still on standby.

210
00:11:44.020 --> 00:11:45.600
Hurry!

211
00:11:45.600 --> 00:11:47.730
Run to the evacuation ship!

212
00:11:51.190 --> 00:11:53.690
So this is a poneglyph?

213
00:11:53.690 --> 00:11:58.200
Yeah. Apparently, even explosives
won't put a scratch on this thing.

214
00:11:58.660 --> 00:12:00.320
What a creepy stone.

215
00:12:00.320 --> 00:12:03.740
I can't believe these things
are scattered around the world.

216
00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:05.290
Is that right?

217
00:12:05.290 --> 00:12:07.710
Yes, they will receive the death penalty.

218
00:12:08.370 --> 00:12:11.880
We've seized all the evidence,
so now we'll carry out your next order.

219
00:12:12.210 --> 00:12:13.500
It cannot be helped.

220
00:12:13.840 --> 00:12:18.470
This is quite unfortunate;
however, they violated the world's laws.

221
00:12:18.470 --> 00:12:20.680
We cannot overlook it.

222
00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:24.430
Cut the transparent pleasantries, Five Elders!

223
00:12:24.430 --> 00:12:25.390
Wha...?!

224
00:12:25.390 --> 00:12:26.890
Don't be rude!

225
00:12:26.890 --> 00:12:29.850
You're talking to the leaders of the world!

226
00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:33.690
Is this Ohara's Professor Clover,
the eminent authority on archaeology?

227
00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:39.150
Your reputation precedes you,
given your world-renowned cultural contributions.

228
00:12:39.150 --> 00:12:42.490
To think that someone of your caliber
would take the wrong path...

229
00:12:42.490 --> 00:12:45.370
The past belongs to all mankind.

230
00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:52.540
No one has the right to stop us
from wanting to know our unspoken history!

231
00:12:52.540 --> 00:12:53.500
Professor...

232
00:12:53.500 --> 00:12:57.760
Deciphering the poneglyphs makes it
possible to revive the ancient weapon,

233
00:12:57.760 --> 00:12:59.760
bringing danger upon this world.

234
00:13:00.970 --> 00:13:06.100
Though your intentions are pure, it only takes
one person to find and abuse your research.

235
00:13:07.470 --> 00:13:13.270
No matter what happened in the past,
we must accept it as our shared history.

236
00:13:13.690 --> 00:13:18.360
If we fearlessly learn all we can,
we will be ready for any future incidents.

237
00:13:18.360 --> 00:13:19.610
How idealistic.

238
00:13:19.610 --> 00:13:21.070
Is that so?

239
00:13:21.070 --> 00:13:24.530
Isn't that reasoning
just a convenient excuse for you?

240
00:13:25.450 --> 00:13:28.580
Of the remaining unanswered
questions about this world,

241
00:13:28.580 --> 00:13:34.920
we are most interested in the poneglyphs
and the very reason for their existence.

242
00:13:35.340 --> 00:13:42.130
Why would the ancients take the trouble to etch their
messages for future generations on such durable stone...

243
00:13:42.130 --> 00:13:46.760
inscribing history upon unbreakable stones
and scattering them around the world?

244
00:13:46.760 --> 00:13:54.940
Is it not because they thought that their message
would be eradicated if they wrote it on paper or in books?

245
00:13:54.940 --> 00:14:00.860
In short, it's proof that those who left
the poneglyphs most certainly had an enemy.

246
00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:06.200
What are you trying to say, Professor Clover?

247
00:14:06.200 --> 00:14:11.370
If we assume these people
were destroyed by said enemy,

248
00:14:11.370 --> 00:14:14.960
then that enemy would have lived on,
unopposed, in the years to follow.

249
00:14:16.790 --> 00:14:23.010
Coincidentally, just when the Void Century
ended 800 years ago...

250
00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:27.720
the World Government was founded.

251
00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:35.100
If the current World Government was once
the enemy of those that ceased to exist,

252
00:14:35.100 --> 00:14:42.650
then the Void Century might be an inconvenient history,
brushed under the rug by those in power.

253
00:14:42.650 --> 00:14:48.370
By analyzing the ancient documents
and what poneglyphs we could find,

254
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:52.330
we eventually discovered
evidence of a lost civilization.

255
00:14:52.330 --> 00:14:58.170
The documents brought to light
that there once existed a grand kingdom.

256
00:14:58.170 --> 00:15:01.170
It seems to have boasted
hegemony in its time,

257
00:15:01.170 --> 00:15:05.470
but information on this country
has been rewritten into oblivion.

258
00:15:05.470 --> 00:15:11.640
They likely anticipated defeat at the hands of the allied
nations who later became the World Government,

259
00:15:11.640 --> 00:15:16.850
and so they inscribed their truth
upon those stones for future generations.

260
00:15:17.350 --> 00:15:21.320
Indeed, those stones are the poneglyphs
that remain to this very day.

261
00:15:22.070 --> 00:15:23.360
I see.

262
00:15:23.360 --> 00:15:25.150
Quite a bold hypothesis...

263
00:15:25.150 --> 00:15:28.780
It's true that the ancient weapon
would threaten the world.

264
00:15:28.780 --> 00:15:34.580
However, isn't it actually that
the World Government is more threatened

265
00:15:34.580 --> 00:15:39.880
by people becoming aware
of that kingdom's existence and ideology?

266
00:15:41.630 --> 00:15:45.130
We have yet to fully analyze
the nature of this threat,

267
00:15:45.130 --> 00:15:48.640
but this once-prosperous kingdom
is the key to everything!

268
00:15:52.470 --> 00:15:53.470
Eliminate him!

269
00:16:03.820 --> 00:16:06.240
Professor!

270
00:16:08.990 --> 00:16:10.700
Ohara...

271
00:16:14.160 --> 00:16:15.950
You bastards!

272
00:16:14.830 --> 00:16:15.950
How dare you...!

273
00:16:15.950 --> 00:16:18.210
– Professor Clover!
– Professor Clover!

274
00:16:18.620 --> 00:16:21.000
...has learned too much.

275
00:16:23.050 --> 00:16:25.170
Signal the attack.

276
00:16:25.920 --> 00:16:28.010
Don't move!

277
00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:30.390
No one leaves the island.

278
00:16:37.480 --> 00:16:42.690
Now, with this golden transponder snail,
which Admiral Sengoku has entrusted to me...

279
00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:43.770
Professor!

280
00:16:43.770 --> 00:16:45.530
Robin...

281
00:16:45.530 --> 00:16:48.150
You fool! You shouldn't be here.

282
00:16:48.150 --> 00:16:49.150
Run!

283
00:16:49.150 --> 00:16:51.160
I'll initiate a buster call!

284
00:16:51.740 --> 00:16:53.280
It's out of my hands now.

285
00:16:54.450 --> 00:16:56.410
He did something!

286
00:16:57.660 --> 00:17:00.620
Hurry to the evacuation ship, Robin.

287
00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:02.580
No! I don't wanna be alone!

288
00:17:02.580 --> 00:17:06.000
This is no time for foolish sentiments!

289
00:17:07.460 --> 00:17:08.630
Robin...

290
00:17:09.970 --> 00:17:14.390
<b>Silver Transponder Snail
Receiver for the Golden Transponder Snail</b>

291
00:17:11.970 --> 00:17:14.390
That's the buster call order!

292
00:17:14.760 --> 00:17:16.640
All battleships, to your positions!

293
00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:18.140
Prepare to open fire!

294
00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:21.400
Hey...

295
00:17:22.020 --> 00:17:23.020
Look!

296
00:17:24.110 --> 00:17:25.900
The Tree of Knowledge is on fire!

297
00:17:26.530 --> 00:17:29.320
Hey, World Government! What are you doing?!

298
00:17:29.320 --> 00:17:32.950
Taking our lives should be enough!

299
00:17:32.950 --> 00:17:36.700
Don't look at me. It must've caught fire
from the explosions earlier.

300
00:17:39.290 --> 00:17:40.620
This isn't a joke!

301
00:17:40.620 --> 00:17:44.080
Do you have any idea how many
scholarly treasures are in there?

302
00:17:43.210 --> 00:17:44.710
Hey! Don't move!

303
00:17:44.710 --> 00:17:47.170
Listen. We don't need guns anymore.

304
00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:50.840
Government agents, clear out!

305
00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:53.890
Hurry up and get the books!

306
00:17:55.890 --> 00:17:57.890
Put out the fire in the library!

307
00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:10.360
Form a bucket brigade!

308
00:18:12.110 --> 00:18:14.110
Get the books outside!

309
00:18:28.550 --> 00:18:30.590
Bring that woman with us.

310
00:18:31.630 --> 00:18:32.380
Come on.

311
00:18:34.220 --> 00:18:37.550
There's a piece of information that only she knows.

312
00:18:38.430 --> 00:18:40.020
We can't have her dying here.

313
00:18:44.310 --> 00:18:45.440
Mommy.

314
00:18:49.440 --> 00:18:51.320
Robin...!

315
00:18:51.320 --> 00:18:54.070
Please... make sure you escape.

316
00:18:54.070 --> 00:18:56.410
Don't die, no matter what!

317
00:18:57.280 --> 00:18:58.700
Nose! Nose!

318
00:19:02.330 --> 00:19:04.540
Robin, make haste!

319
00:19:04.540 --> 00:19:06.460
Hurry and leave!

320
00:19:10.300 --> 00:19:12.130
– Robin!
– Robin!

321
00:19:20.260 --> 00:19:23.230
Are you... my mom?

322
00:19:28.730 --> 00:19:31.690
Olvia! Are you coming aboard or not?

323
00:19:31.690 --> 00:19:33.650
Mommy!

324
00:19:33.650 --> 00:19:35.820
I'll hold her, so go already!

325
00:19:34.950 --> 00:19:35.820
Mommy!

326
00:19:35.820 --> 00:19:37.320
Don't go!

327
00:19:37.320 --> 00:19:41.740
Mommy! Mommy! Mommy!

328
00:19:41.830 --> 00:19:43.620
I'm sorry, Robin.

329
00:19:43.620 --> 00:19:46.290
I can never call myself your mother again.

330
00:19:46.830 --> 00:19:52.170
After all these years,
I shouldn't even think about it.

331
00:20:00.430 --> 00:20:03.010
– Monster!
– Monster!

332
00:20:03.060 --> 00:20:05.730
Her mom abandoned her!

333
00:20:05.770 --> 00:20:08.520
Robin! Those are my daughter's clothes!

334
00:20:08.520 --> 00:20:11.110
I'm sorry, Aunt Roji!
I wanted to try them on just once!

335
00:20:11.150 --> 00:20:14.320
You eat an awful lot for a freeloader.

336
00:20:22.780 --> 00:20:25.120
Are you...

337
00:20:26.910 --> 00:20:28.670
my mother?!

338
00:20:34.840 --> 00:20:37.590
What? You have a child?

339
00:20:39.760 --> 00:20:40.890
No.

340
00:20:41.470 --> 00:20:42.970
Olvia...

341
00:20:43.720 --> 00:20:45.390
I'm sorry...

342
00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:49.940
but I think you're confusing me
with someone else.

343
00:20:50.770 --> 00:20:55.440
I can't let you become known
as a criminal's daughter!

344
00:20:55.440 --> 00:20:57.400
Olvia...

345
00:20:57.860 --> 00:20:59.530
What a weird brat.

346
00:21:00.110 --> 00:21:01.490
Hey, let's go!

347
00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:19.130
I'm Robin!

348
00:21:19.130 --> 00:21:23.470
I've grown, but don't you remember me?!

349
00:21:23.470 --> 00:21:26.310
I've waited so long for you to come home!

350
00:21:26.310 --> 00:21:27.720
Are you...

351
00:21:29.480 --> 00:21:30.890
really not...

352
00:21:32.150 --> 00:21:33.400
my mother?

353
00:21:35.150 --> 00:21:37.900
I wanted you...

354
00:21:37.900 --> 00:21:39.570
to hold my hand...

355
00:21:40.900 --> 00:21:43.490
and walk with me someday.

356
00:21:43.490 --> 00:21:48.540
So I studied hard and was
able to become an archaeologist!

357
00:21:48.540 --> 00:21:50.830
I can read poneglyphs, too!

358
00:21:52.370 --> 00:21:53.920
That brat can do what?!

359
00:21:53.920 --> 00:21:55.460
Stop it, Robin!

360
00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:57.340
So...

361
00:21:57.340 --> 00:22:00.340
please let me stay by your side!

362
00:22:00.340 --> 00:22:02.090
Mom!

363
00:22:02.970 --> 00:22:04.340
Robin...!

364
00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:06.760
Please...

365
00:22:08.270 --> 00:22:09.470
don't leave me...

366
00:22:10.810 --> 00:22:12.730
alone anymore!

367
00:22:17.940 --> 00:22:18.730
What?!

368
00:22:19.110 --> 00:22:21.360
Why the hell are they attacking us?!

369
00:22:21.360 --> 00:22:23.200
I'm exercising a buster call.

370
00:22:24.030 --> 00:22:26.450
Commence concerted fire!

371
00:22:26.450 --> 00:22:30.660
We're targeting everything on Ohara,
the island of archaeology!

372
00:22:30.660 --> 00:22:35.920
The research by the Oharan scholars has
reached a level we never imagined.

373
00:22:35.920 --> 00:22:39.500
Knowledge can be transferred.
Don't let it leave that island.

374
00:22:40.420 --> 00:22:45.590
In the name of justice,
annihilate the devils of Ohara!

375
00:22:49.720 --> 00:22:52.270
Dammit! What's going on?!

376
00:22:52.270 --> 00:22:56.480
We haven't gotten off of the island yet!
Are they trying to kill us?!

377
00:22:57.690 --> 00:23:00.230
The Tree of Knowledge is taking direct hits!

378
00:23:00.230 --> 00:23:02.690
The military might of Marine Headquarters...

379
00:23:02.690 --> 00:23:05.950
The government must have been
planning to do this all along.

380
00:23:05.950 --> 00:23:06.990
How senseless.

381
00:23:06.990 --> 00:23:10.370
Chief, the brat said she's an archaeologist.

382
00:23:10.370 --> 00:23:14.000
Yeah, she did say that,
though I don't know whether it's true.

383
00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:16.710
Eliminate her too, just in case.

384
00:23:16.710 --> 00:23:19.920
Remember her face and ensure
she doesn't escape the island.

385
00:23:19.920 --> 00:23:21.250
Let's move!

386
00:23:21.250 --> 00:23:22.550
I'll take Olvia with–

387
00:23:24.170 --> 00:23:27.510
Forget her! No time for that now!
Just leave her here!

388
00:23:27.510 --> 00:23:30.350
If we stick around any longer,
we're goners too!

389
00:23:30.350 --> 00:23:33.060
And my life is the most important of all!

390
00:23:33.060 --> 00:23:34.560
Full retreat!

391
00:23:34.560 --> 00:23:35.850
Get back to the ship!

392
00:23:44.240 --> 00:23:46.450
Do something about the fire in the library!

393
00:23:46.450 --> 00:23:48.570
Protect the Tree of Knowledge!

394
00:24:09.800 --> 00:24:11.390
I've wanted this...

395
00:24:14.520 --> 00:24:16.600
for so long!

396
00:24:19.560 --> 00:24:21.110
Robin!

397
00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:25.570
Mom!

398
00:24:28.860 --> 00:24:31.570
It's my fault, Robin.

399
00:24:32.200 --> 00:24:35.540
Is it true that you can read poneglyphs?

400
00:24:36.450 --> 00:24:39.710
If I had properly kept an eye on you...

401
00:24:40.250 --> 00:24:42.000
I’m sorry.

402
00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.000
I just wanted–

403
00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:46.840
I can't believe how capable you've become!

404
00:24:46.840 --> 00:24:48.170
I'm so proud of you!

405
00:24:48.550 --> 00:24:51.050
You must've tried hard and studied a lot.

406
00:24:51.930 --> 00:24:54.180
It's not something just anyone can do.

407
00:24:54.180 --> 00:24:55.930
You're amazing, Robin!

408
00:25:02.480 --> 00:25:06.940
Fortunately, the officials from earlier
are the only ones who know about it.

409
00:25:06.940 --> 00:25:09.320
This is no time to be sitting around here.

410
00:25:09.320 --> 00:25:11.870
Olvia! Take Robin and run!

411
00:25:11.870 --> 00:25:16.370
If you can sneak Robin aboard
the evacuation ship, she can leave the island!

412
00:25:20.040 --> 00:25:20.870
Robin!

413
00:25:20.870 --> 00:25:23.540
There you are! I looked all over for you!

414
00:25:23.540 --> 00:25:24.710
Saul!

415
00:25:24.710 --> 00:25:26.840
So you were able to see Olvia!

416
00:25:26.840 --> 00:25:27.710
Saul!

417
00:25:27.710 --> 00:25:29.800
What are you doing on this island?!

418
00:25:29.800 --> 00:25:35.560
By some twist of fate, I got shipwrecked
and was saved by Robin on the beach.

419
00:25:35.560 --> 00:25:37.810
Anyway, the situation is really bad!

420
00:25:37.810 --> 00:25:40.020
You have to leave the island immediately!

421
00:25:40.480 --> 00:25:41.520
Please take Robin!

422
00:25:41.520 --> 00:25:43.770
My daughter must escape the island!

423
00:25:43.770 --> 00:25:44.860
What?!

424
00:25:44.860 --> 00:25:46.730
No! What about you, Mom?!

425
00:25:46.730 --> 00:25:48.150
Aren't you coming with me?!

426
00:25:49.360 --> 00:25:50.570
Olvia, what are you...?

427
00:25:51.070 --> 00:25:53.530
There's still something
that I have to do here, so...

428
00:25:53.530 --> 00:25:56.030
Mom! Don't leave me!

429
00:25:56.030 --> 00:25:57.700
I finally got to see you again!

430
00:25:57.700 --> 00:25:59.120
I'll stay here too!

431
00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:00.460
Robin...

432
00:26:01.040 --> 00:26:04.040
As an Oharan scholar,
you should understand this well.

433
00:26:04.040 --> 00:26:06.000
History is the legacy of mankind.

434
00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:09.340
It will illuminate the future for your generation.

435
00:26:09.340 --> 00:26:11.800
But the history we obtained from the past...

436
00:26:12.340 --> 00:26:15.680
will disappear unless
we pass it on to the next era.

437
00:26:15.680 --> 00:26:16.510
Put out the fire!

438
00:26:16.510 --> 00:26:17.640
Protect the books!

439
00:26:18.260 --> 00:26:21.520
Ohara doesn't want to expose our history.

440
00:26:21.520 --> 00:26:24.100
We only wished to preserve
the voices of the past.

441
00:26:24.850 --> 00:26:27.570
Our research ends here...

442
00:26:28.270 --> 00:26:30.490
but even if Ohara is obliterated...

443
00:26:32.150 --> 00:26:37.240
we cannot forsake
the future of your generation!

444
00:26:38.240 --> 00:26:40.250
I don't understand!

445
00:26:41.700 --> 00:26:44.120
You will... someday.

446
00:26:46.840 --> 00:26:49.250
Now, go, Saul!

447
00:26:51.840 --> 00:26:53.090
Are you sure about this?

448
00:26:53.420 --> 00:26:54.180
Yes.

449
00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:58.470
I don't wanna go!
I wanna stay with you, Mom!

450
00:26:58.890 --> 00:27:01.310
Mom!

451
00:27:01.310 --> 00:27:04.140
I was happy to hear you call me that.

452
00:27:04.940 --> 00:27:06.310
Thank you!

453
00:27:07.110 --> 00:27:10.150
From now on, for you and me both...

454
00:27:10.150 --> 00:27:11.440
Live, Robin!

455
00:27:29.000 --> 00:27:29.630
What?!

456
00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:31.750
Vice Admiral! Vice Admiral Kuzan!

457
00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:33.090
What?!

458
00:27:33.090 --> 00:27:35.720
On the island... Yes, there's no doubt about it!

459
00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:37.720
What's the matter?!

460
00:27:37.720 --> 00:27:39.390
Just spit it out!

461
00:27:39.390 --> 00:27:42.060
It's the deserter, Vice Admiral Saul!

462
00:27:42.060 --> 00:27:44.390
Saul! Go back! Please!

463
00:27:44.390 --> 00:27:46.640
No! I can't do that!

464
00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:49.650
Robin! Hold your head high, Robin!

465
00:27:49.650 --> 00:27:51.570
Your mom is honorable!

466
00:27:51.570 --> 00:27:53.610
Ohara is honorable!

467
00:27:53.610 --> 00:27:58.110
Someday, pass down
this island's history, Robin!

468
00:27:58.110 --> 00:28:01.870
Ohara fought against the world!

469
00:28:04.450 --> 00:28:05.910
Stop it!

470
00:28:05.910 --> 00:28:07.500
Capturing them is enough!

471
00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:12.880
They aren't exactly bloodthirsty pirates!
Are you too weak to capture them alive?!

472
00:28:13.550 --> 00:28:16.720
We've captured many ships
that were on history expeditions,

473
00:28:16.720 --> 00:28:20.680
but I don't understand
why this crew had to die.

474
00:28:21.010 --> 00:28:24.390
Vice Admiral Saul! We found a lone survivor!

475
00:28:25.100 --> 00:28:26.600
You killed my associates!

476
00:28:28.020 --> 00:28:30.560
Do you really want the weapon?

477
00:28:30.940 --> 00:28:32.020
What pitiful people...

478
00:28:32.650 --> 00:28:34.570
You're just tools, yet you judge us...

479
00:28:34.570 --> 00:28:36.030
Hey! He's a vice admiral!

480
00:28:36.030 --> 00:28:39.530
...blindly believing your justice
prevents the weapon's revival!

481
00:28:40.620 --> 00:28:45.620
You're terrified of a history
you don't even understand!

482
00:28:46.160 --> 00:28:47.620
This is a top-secret mission.

483
00:28:47.620 --> 00:28:49.790
A buster call?

484
00:28:50.210 --> 00:28:55.340
Five vice admirals command ten battleships
in an all-out assault, and I want you to be one of them.

485
00:28:55.340 --> 00:28:57.090
They are just scholars!

486
00:28:57.090 --> 00:28:59.090
Why do we have to go that far?

487
00:28:59.090 --> 00:29:05.100
Even all the ones we've captured just
seemed really intent on studying history!

488
00:29:05.100 --> 00:29:09.060
If their research is dangerous,
the government should help them out!

489
00:29:09.060 --> 00:29:11.980
My men and I will be
the ones taking their lives...

490
00:29:12.310 --> 00:29:15.400
so give me some kind of proof
that they're evil!

491
00:29:15.400 --> 00:29:18.440
Are you doubting the government?
Shut up and follow orders!

492
00:29:23.410 --> 00:29:24.990
I'd like...

493
00:29:25.830 --> 00:29:27.200
to ask you some questions.

494
00:29:27.200 --> 00:29:31.170
This is an emergency! Vice Admiral Saul
took a criminal and deserted!

495
00:29:32.170 --> 00:29:35.630
He knows everything about the operation.

496
00:29:35.960 --> 00:29:38.840
After them! Capture Saul and Olvia without fail!

497
00:29:39.470 --> 00:29:40.970
Shoot them if needed!

498
00:29:41.590 --> 00:29:42.840
We're being chased!

499
00:29:42.840 --> 00:29:44.800
I'll handle them!

500
00:29:44.800 --> 00:29:47.770
You'll never be able
to return to the Marines, Saul.

501
00:29:47.770 --> 00:29:49.020
That's fine.

502
00:29:49.020 --> 00:29:52.730
I can't stay in the Marines
if I can't even trust them.

503
00:29:53.100 --> 00:29:57.360
This may be a government-sanctioned action,
but this operation is too tyrannical.

504
00:29:57.360 --> 00:29:59.610
I need to follow my own sense of justice.

505
00:29:59.610 --> 00:30:02.450
Now, hurry to your homeland
to inform everyone.

506
00:30:02.450 --> 00:30:04.070
I'm not thanking you for this.

507
00:30:04.070 --> 00:30:06.160
Good luck.

508
00:30:09.620 --> 00:30:11.290
Fire!

509
00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:16.540
They're aiming at me!

510
00:30:20.840 --> 00:30:22.550
Saul!

511
00:30:22.550 --> 00:30:24.010
Oh! It hit him!

512
00:30:24.010 --> 00:30:25.090
I'm sorry!

513
00:30:25.090 --> 00:30:28.470
Don't apologize! He's already
an accomplice of those evildoers!

514
00:30:28.470 --> 00:30:30.480
I'm sorry, Robin.

515
00:30:30.480 --> 00:30:32.480
That must've scared you.

516
00:30:33.770 --> 00:30:35.650
Hold on a sec.

517
00:30:36.020 --> 00:30:37.020
It was you...!

518
00:30:37.020 --> 00:30:38.400
Firing at this close range?!

519
00:30:38.400 --> 00:30:41.610
What if you had hurt Robin?!

520
00:30:42.030 --> 00:30:43.530
Vice Admiral! Please stop!

521
00:30:43.530 --> 00:30:44.740
What are you doing?!

522
00:30:44.740 --> 00:30:49.620
I don't know what justice is in this situation,
but I know I should protect my friend!

523
00:30:49.620 --> 00:30:51.830
Stop it! Saul!

524
00:30:52.210 --> 00:30:53.580
Get ready!

525
00:30:53.580 --> 00:31:00.250
Making an enemy of me
will be the last thing you do!

526
00:31:11.940 --> 00:31:18.480
I know there’s something that I need to say,

527
00:31:18.860 --> 00:31:22.450
but I can’t seem to find the words

528
00:31:22.700 --> 00:31:30.330
Wandering aimlessly, forever on the hunt, that’s how I’ve lived

529
00:31:30.330 --> 00:31:36.090
And now there’s something right in front of me,

530
00:31:37.290 --> 00:31:40.800
a light that shines brighter than gold

531
00:31:41.170 --> 00:31:46.180
But as I trail behind, it speeds out of sight.

532
00:31:46.180 --> 00:31:52.770
What’s going on? Scared of what’s yet to come

533
00:31:53.100 --> 00:31:59.020
So many times, so many times as we both stumbled on the way

534
00:31:59.230 --> 00:32:02.030
We’ve had our highs, we’ve had our lows;

535
00:32:02.320 --> 00:32:05.110
Yeah, we just take it day by day

536
00:32:05.410 --> 00:32:11.660
Never forget that even when the night snuffs out the light

537
00:32:11.950 --> 00:32:18.290
When the dark has passed the sun will rise again
